                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5>Recipe 1: Pasta Primavera</h5>
                        <p>A light and flavorful pasta dish with seasonal vegetables.</p>
                        <h3>Ingredients:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>1 pound pasta (e.g., penne, farfalle)</li>
                            <li>1 tablespoon olive oil</li>
                            <li>1 onion, chopped</li>
                            <li>2 cloves garlic, minced</li>
                            <li>2 cups assorted vegetables (e.g., broccoli, peas, carrots), chopped</li>
                            <li>1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved</li>
                            <li>1/2 cup crumbled feta cheese (optional)</li>
                            <li>1/4 cup fresh basil leaves, chopped</li>
                            <li>Salt and pepper to taste</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-10 offset-md-1 mt-2">
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5>Recipe 2: Chicken Curry</h5>
                        <p>Aromatic and comforting curry with tender chicken and creamy sauce.</p>
                        <h3>Ingredients:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>1 pound boneless, skinless chicken breasts, cut into bite-sized pieces</li>
                            <li>1 tablespoon vegetable oil</li>
                            <li>1 onion, chopped</li>
                            <li>2 cloves garlic, minced</li>
                            <li>1 tablespoon curry powder</li>
                            <li>1 teaspoon ground ginger</li>
                            <li>1 (14.5 oz) can diced tomatoes, undrained</li>
                            <li>1 (13.5 oz) can coconut milk</li>
                            <li>1 tablespoon soy sauce</li>
                            <li>Salt and pepper to taste</li>
                            <li>Cooked rice (for serving)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-10 offset-md-1 mt-2">
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5>Recipe 3: Vegetarian Chili</h5>
                        <p>Hearty and flavorful chili packed with beans, vegetables, and spices.</p>
                        <h3>Ingredients:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>1 tablespoon olive oil</li>
                            <li>1 onion, chopped</li>
                            <li>2 cloves garlic, minced</li>
                            <li>1 green bell pepper, chopped</li>
                            <li>1 (15 oz) can kidney beans, drained and rinsed</li>
                            <li>1 (15 oz) can black beans, drained and rinsed</li>
                            <li>1 (14.5 oz) can diced tomatoes, undrained</li>
                            <li>1 (15 oz) can corn, drained</li>
                            <li>2 cups vegetable broth</li>
                            <li>1 tablespoon chili powder</li>
                            <li>1 teaspoon cumin</li>
                            <li>½ teaspoon smoked paprika</li>
                            <li>Salt and pepper to taste</li>
                            <li>Optional toppings: shredded cheese, sour cream, chopped avocado</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
